 38  def comparison [is_right_adjoint R] : D ⥤ algebra ((left_adjoint R) ⋙ R) :=

 41    { A := R.obj X,
 42      a := R.map (h.counit.app X),

 61  /-- A functor is *reflective*, or *a reflective inclusion*, if it is fully faithful and right adjoint. -/
 62  class reflective (R : D ⥤ C) extends is_right_adjoint R, full R, faithful R.
 63  
 64  /-- A right adjoint functor `R : D ⥤ C` is *monadic* if the comparison function `monad.comparison R` from `D` to the
 65  category of Eilenberg-Moore algebras for the adjunction is an equivalence. -/
 66  class monadic_right_adjoint (R : D ⥤ C) extends is_right_adjoint R :=
